        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Meanwhile, in Manchin’s state of West Virginia, 80 percent of the population makes less than $86,600. Those households would receive a combined total of $2.5 billion from the checks — and the bottom 20 percent of West Virginia income earners would see a 33 percent boost in their income.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In all three states — as in the entire country as a whole — the richest 1 percent would receive no benefits from the checks.",
